HEADWORD: Purim
<hw>Pu"rim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>p⟦umac⟧r</ets>, pl. <ets>p⟦umac⟧r⟦imac⟧m</ets>, a lot.]</ety>
<def>A Jewish festival, called also the Feast of Lots, instituted to
commemorate the deliverance of the Jews from the machinations of
Haman.</def> <rj><au>Esther ix. 26.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

